The police command in Lagos State has arrested a fish farmer, Jeremiah Obifor, 61, for allegedly cutting off the hand of an 11-year-old boy, Goodluck Amechi. The spokesman of the police in Lagos State, DSP Bala Elkana, said in a statement in Lagos on Sunday that the man cut off the boy’s hand whom he suspected had come to steal his fish. Elkana said the suspect was arrested after the victim’s foster mother, Doris Isaac, reported the matter at the Okoko, Police Station. He said that on June 7 at about 12:20 pm the boy’s foster mother, who resided at No. 6 Ajanaku Street, Okoko, reported the matter at the Okoko police station. The police spokesman said Obifor attacked the 11-year-old boy with a machete. “The victim was rushed to Igando General Hospital. “The suspect alleged that he saw the victim around his fish pond and thought that he came to steal his fish and that was why he attacked him. “Investigation is ongoing and the suspect will be charged to court,” he said. (NAN)  Man mistakes 11-year-old boy for thief, cuts off his hand Clergyman arrested for allegedly infecting minors with HIV in Lagos Teenage robbery suspect arrested over attack on petrol station Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin